            <title>0.8.6</title>
            <pubDate>Fri, 24 Jul 2026 11:38:01 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>806</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.6</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.6</h2>
<p><b>Sign in with Google — no API key to set up.</b> Jarvis now reaches its AI through a
secure shared service instead of asking you to paste an API key. Open the app, sign in with
your Google account, and you're in — the key stays server-side and never ships inside the app.
Access is controlled by an allowlist, so only approved accounts can sign in.</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Google sign-in</b> — one click to start; the in-app API-key screen is gone.</li>
  <li><b>Telegram sync is steadier</b> — it now waits for Telegram to be fully ready before
      syncing, so it no longer fails and needs a manual retry after a restart or crash.</li>
</ul>
<p>Everything still runs and searches privately on your Mac; only the AI calls go through the
shared service.</p>
]]></description>
